radiographic_examinations.findings: Marked supratentorial hydrocephalus with a normal-sized fourth ventricle, marked thinning of brain parenchyma with no evidence of acute infarction or intracranial hemorrhage, severe thinning of the corpus callosum, enlarged posterior fossa with hypoplasia of cerebellar vermis, and brainstem kinked to Z shaped.
Worsening of the supratentorial hydrocephalus with posterior fossa cysts.
